snippet.textDisplay: Okay, been debating whether to share this or not, but I might as well just throw it up here and see what happens. This is a teaser/proof of concept that I put together for a short film that fell apart for a number of reasons (money) back in 2007. It was my first foray into using Blender. Actually, it was my first attempt at 3D anything outside of solids in After Effects. I was really happy with the results, but haven't had time to revisit Blender since. Probably time I did though. Anyway, feel free to critique. https://youtu.be/rbNRIbPKuco

snippet.textDisplay: I feel like, yes, digital backgrounds might not have been possible for every shot in 1999-2003, hence the miniatures, but I think these shots look way more realistic than most fully CGI backgrounds look these days. I think VFX work best when perfecting an already existing special effects shot and used sparingly otherwise, not when everything is completely CGI.
snippet.textOriginal: I feel like, yes, digital backgrounds might not have been possible for every shot in 1999-2003, hence the miniatures, but I think these shots look way more realistic than most fully CGI backgrounds look these days. I think VFX work best when perfecting an already existing special effects shot and used sparingly otherwise, not when everything is completely CGI.
